Only MudSelect uses `OnFocusOutAsync`. Now let me understand the exact fix needed.

The key method in `MudBaseInput` that does the validation on blur is `OnBlurredAsync`:

```csharp
protected internal virtual async Task OnBlurredAsync(FocusEventArgs obj)
{
    _isFocused = false;
    if (ReadOnly) return;

    if (!OnlyValidateIfDirty || _isDirty)
    {
        Touched = true;
        if (_validated) { ... invoke OnBlur ... }
        else { ... await BeginValidationAfterAsync(...) or await ValidateValue() ... }
    }
}
```

The `MudSelect` needs to call something similar to `OnBlurredAsync` when focus leaves it but the popover is closed. Since `MudSelect` inherits from `MudBaseInput<T>`, it can call `OnBlurredAsync` directly... BUT the `MudBaseInput.OnBlurredAsync` checks `if (ReadOnly) return;` — but `ReadOnly` on `MudSelect` is not necessarily true.

